token name OPOSSUM (opos)

System Architecture Draft

1. Core Components
	1.	BondingCurveSale Contract
	•	This single contract will:
	•	Hold a pre-funded balance of your existing ERC20 tokens (the “vaulted” approach).
	•	Implement the bonding curve logic (closed-form math for buy/sell).
	•	Collect and distribute fees.
	•	Interact with Uniswap (v3 or future v4) via the INonfungiblePositionManager-like interface to manage liquidity positions.
	2.	Existing ERC20 Token
	•	Pre-deployed contract.
	•	You’ll transfer (e.g.) up to 1 billion tokens into the BondingCurveSale contract at deployment time.
	•	When users buy, the sale contract sends tokens out; when they sell, tokens flow back in.
	3.	Uniswap Position NFT
	•	The BondingCurveSale contract will own one (or more) liquidity position(s).
	•	Each buy or sell can trigger re-centering of the liquidity range ±5% around the current price.
	4.	Admin/Owner Wallet
	•	Can adjust certain parameters (e.g., fee recipient address, base price, re-centering logic).
	•	Can withdraw leftover WBTC or ETH from the contract if needed (subject to your rules).
	5.	Fee Recipient Wallet
	•	Receives the 5% buy fee and 10% sell fee immediately (or the contract can accumulate and send it out each transaction).

2. State Variables & Configuration

Inside the BondingCurveSale contract, we’ll track:
	1.	Token Balances
	•	tokenAddress (the ERC20 being sold).
	•	The contract’s own balance of that token. (Increases when users sell, decreases when users buy.)
	2.	Bonding Curve Tracking
	•	basePrice (￼): The starting price in ETH or a pegged value.
	•	totalSold or N: Tracks how many net tokens have been sold via the bonding curve (buys - sells).
	•	For fractional token amounts, N can be a floating-point scaled integer (e.g., a fixed-point representation).
	3.	Fees
	•	buyFeeBP = 5 (5% basis points).
	•	sellFeeBP = 10 (10% basis points).
	•	feeRecipient: The address that receives fees.
	4.	Uniswap Liquidity
	•	positionManager: Address of the Uniswap (v3-like) NonfungiblePositionManager.
	•	poolFee: The Uniswap pool fee tier (e.g., 0.3%).
	•	wbtcAddress: Address of the WBTC token.
	•	currentPositionId: The NFT ID representing the active liquidity position.
	•	A structure to track tickLower and tickUpper that define ±5% range around the current price.
	5.	Other Bookkeeping
	•	reentrancyGuard: A simple modifier to prevent reentrant calls.
	•	Possibly an “oracle price feed” if you want a reference for the base price in terms of ETH vs. USD (optional, if you want it dynamic).

